BlackUnicorn - PNG Chunk Overflow Attack

This is a malicious security test fixture that demonstrates PNG chunk overflow vulnerability.

Attack Description:
The attacker crafts a PNG image with an IHDR chunk containing an oversized width/height value that causes integer overflow during image allocation. By manipulating the chunk length field, the attacker can cause buffer overflow and execute arbitrary code.

Malicious PNG Structure:
- PNG Signature: 89 50 4E 47 0D 0A 1A 0A (valid)
- IHDR chunk length: 0xFFFFFFFF (malicious - max uint32)
- Payload width: 0x7FFFFFFF (max int32)
- Payload height: 0x7FFFFFFF (max int32)
- This causes malloc(size) to overflow and allocate insufficient memory
- Subsequent image data write causes heap buffer overflow

Detection: Chunk overflow, buffer overflow, memory corruption, heap overflow, integer overflow
